.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-BLOCK-HEIGHT" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-block-height \- show current Bitcoin block height seen by the node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-block-height
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns the most recent Bitcoin block height reported by
.B lightning-cli getinfo
as
.BR blockheight .
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"blockheight":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-version (1),
.BR lightning-node-health (1)
